    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1948-09-29T17:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1948-09-29T17:00:00-05:00" n="353"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d353">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">124.935: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Acting Secretary of State</gloss> to
                        the Ambassador in China</hi> (<persName type="to">
                        <hi rend="italic">Stuart</hi>
                    </persName>)<note n="86" xml:id="d353fn86">Repeated to the Consul General at
                        Shanghai as No. 1676.</note>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1948-09-29T17:00:00-05:00"
                            >September 29, 1948—5 p.m.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>1371. For Embassy, Casaday and Parker. State and Treas sympathetic Emb desire for
                    flexibility and Emb concern re possibility sudden and severe break in rate
                    (Embtel 1735<note n="87" xml:id="d353fn87">September 20, <ref target="#pg_407"
                            >p. 407</ref>.</note> rptd Shanghai 829). Because importance possible
                    new rate on Army-Navy expenditures and implications for ECA special account,
                    which latter is NAC interest here, would appreciate more info prior
                    consideration your recommendation. Transmit alternative rate formulas under
                    consideration for possible approach Chinese Government.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Lovett</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
